name: avocado mac n cheese
instructions:
1. In large saucepot, cook pasta in salted water according to package directions. Drain and set aside. 

2. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, combine milk, garlic, nutmeg and chili powder. Bring to a boil; reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.

3. When pasta is almost cooked, place in blender the parsley leaves, 1-1/2 avocado, cheese, lime juice and hot milk with garlic cloves; whirl until smooth.

4. Drain pasta and return to sauce pot. Pour cheese sauce over pasta; toss to combine. Add chives and remaining 1/2 avocado (diced); toss gently. Serve hot or at room temperature.
